Ronbot Control Panel — Cursor Rules (v2.1)These rules apply to the Ronbot Control Panel: a production-grade, zero-terminal Electron desktop installer + control panel for the Hermes agent (Nous Research). The app must feel magical for complete novices while remaining 100% faithful to official Hermes behavior.Core Product VisionGoal: Take any user from “nothing installed” to “fully working Hermes agent with channels, skills, browser, and messaging platforms (including WhatsApp)” without ever showing a terminal.
Cross-platform requirement: Must work on Windows, macOS, and Linux.Linux & macOS: native Hermes installer.
Windows: must detect WSL2. If missing, provide one-click guided WSL2 setup (or clear instructions + button that opens the Microsoft WSL installer). All Hermes CLI commands run inside WSL2 when on Windows. Never assume native Windows support.

Hermes fidelity: Every setup flow, command, config key, and behavior must exactly match the official Hermes documentation (https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/). Use only documented hermes CLI commands (hermes install, hermes doctor, hermes whatsapp, hermes gateway install/start/status, hermes skills …, etc.). Never invent custom install methods.
Skills & customization: The existing Skills page must provide guided, novice-friendly wizards for every Hermes skill that requires additional setup or configuration (browser backend, external API integrations, custom tools, etc.). Users must be able to discover, install, update, configure, and enable/disable skills entirely through the UI using the same visual, automated pattern as the WhatsApp wizard.
Novice-first: Every long-running operation (install, pairing, gateway start, WhatsApp QR, skill setup, etc.) must be fully automated with rich progress UI, live logs (streamed), clear success/failure states, and one-click retry/fix buttons.

Stack — do not deviateVite 5 + React 18 + TypeScript 5 + Tailwind 3 + shadcn/ui + framer-motion
Electron 41, packaged with @electron/packager (NOT electron-builder)
Package manager: bun (bun.lockb). Never use npm/pnpm/yarn.
State: React contexts only. No Redux, Zustand, Jotai, Recoil.
Routing: HashRouter only (file:// compatible). Never BrowserRouter.
Vite base: "./" in vite.config.ts is mandatory.

Architecture — never break these patternsAll OS access goes through window.electronAPI → src/lib/systemAPI/*. Never import child_process, fs, path, os in renderer code.
IPC handlers live in electron/main.cjs. Bridge surface is electron/preload.cjs (CommonJS).
Secrets go through secretsStore (src/lib/systemAPI/secretsStore.ts). Never write secrets to ~/.hermes/.env from the UI. Materialize on demand only.
Long-running commands use runCommandStream + onCommandOutput. Always store the unsubscribe function and call it in cleanup.
Managed YAML/config edits use BEGIN/END marker blocks + repair routine. Never free-form edit user files.
Permissions/capabilities are checked via CapabilitiesContext. Never inline checks.
Hermes lifecycle ownership: src/lib/systemAPI/hermes.ts is the single source of truth for all Hermes interactions (install, doctor, platform setup, gateway, skills, config blocks, self-tests). All platform and skill wizards must live in or be called from here.

Hermes-Specific Rules (must follow)Installation flow: On first launch (or via Install page), run the official one-line installer via runCommandStream (detect OS and route to WSL2 on Windows). Show rich progress UI with live output.
Platform connections (WhatsApp, Telegram, etc.): All existing wizards must remain fully automated: run the official hermes <platform> command, capture and display any QR/output visually, detect success via session files + process exit, auto-write required non-secret .env keys, then trigger hermes gateway install + hermes gateway start.
Skills management: Extend the existing Skills page so that every skill listed by hermes skills that requires setup/configuration gets its own guided wizard (visual progress, live logs, automated post-setup config edits, gateway restart if needed). Mirror the WhatsApp wizard pattern exactly: no terminal, no manual steps, clear success state with one-click reconfigure/restart.
Gateway management: Auto-start/stop/status via hermes gateway commands. On app launch, ensure gateway is running. Provide dashboard controls for start/stop/restart + service install status.
.env handling: Platform toggles, skill toggles, and other non-secret config go directly into ~/.hermes/.env (via managed edit in hermes.ts). API keys stay in secretsStore and are materialized only when launching Hermes.
Doctor & self-test: Run hermes doctor after major changes and surface results in UI with fix buttons.
Cross-platform helpers: In src/lib/systemAPI/prereqs.ts and hermes.ts, maintain explicit OS detection and WSL2 routing. All paths must resolve correctly inside WSL2 on Windows.

Design system — token-driven onlyAll colors are HSL CSS variables in src/index.css. Never use raw hex/rgb.
Use semantic Tailwind tokens and existing glass utilities.
Fonts: Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code/logs).

SecurityNever echo secrets in logs.
Never write secrets directly to .env from UI.

Testing & commitsvitest + @testing
-library/react.
Conventional commits.

NeverNever reintroduce Supabase, Lovable Cloud, or any remote backend.
Never run package managers from renderer — always through runCommand.
Never use electron-builder.
Never overwrite user config files blindly.
Never assume native Windows support for Hermes — always route through WSL2 on Windows.
Never expose raw CLI output to the user — always wrap in guided wizards.

App-specific notesRonbot / Hermes: UI may use “Hermes” or “Ronbot” interchangeably (Hermes is preferred where it improves clarity). Agent default name remains “Ron” unless user changes it.
Provider-agnostic: Hermes core is provider-agnostic. All model/API keys are managed via secretsStore.
Existing features: Preserve and extend the already-built Skills tab, cross-platform WSL2 support, WhatsApp wizard, browser setup, and all other guided flows. When adding or improving any skill wizard, follow the exact same visual/automated pattern established by WhatsApp.
CapabilitiesContext: Keep it as the single source of truth for what the agent can do (browser, skills, platforms, etc.).